  "response": "To prepare for CMI (Chennai Mathematical Institute) and ISI (Indian Statistical Institute) entrance tests in 2019, here are some effective strategies:\n\n1. Syllabus and Exam Pattern\n- Thoroughly understand the exam pattern and syllabus\n- Review past years' question papers\n- Identify important topics and their weightage\n\n2. Mathematics Preparation\n- Focus on advanced mathematics topics\n- Study algebra, geometry, number theory, calculus\n- Practice problem-solving skills\n- Solve complex mathematical problems\n\n3. Study Resources\n- Reference standard textbooks\n- Previous years' question papers\n- Online study materials\n- Mathematics olympiad books\n- Coaching institute materials\n\n4. Mock Tests and Practice\n- Take regular mock tests\n- Time yourself during practice\n- Analyze your performance\n- Work on weak areas\n- Improve problem-solving speed\n\n5. Recommended Books\n- Advanced Algebra\n- Geometry books by Challenging Mathematical Problems\n- Number Theory books\n- Reference books for Mathematical Olympiads\n\n6. Additional Tips\n- Develop strong analytical skills\n- Practice mental mathematics\n- Join study groups\n- Solve puzzles and brain teasers\n- Maintain consistent study schedule\n\nConsistent preparation and strategic approach will help you perform well in these competitive entrance tests.",
